				 AllBank profit rises to Rs 240cr
 A STAFF REPORTER				 	 A.C. Mahajan in Calcutta on Wednesday. A Telegraph picture																								Calcutta, Oct. 17: Allahabad Bank today reported a net profit of Rs 239.79 crore for the quarter ended September 30 against Rs 200.39 crore in the corresponding quarter of the previous year. 																								Earnings stood at Rs 440.18 crore during the period compared with Rs 338.28 crore a year ago. 																								Our tax liability was determined under the minimum alternate tax provision until the previous fiscal, as our accumulated loss was higher than our yearly profits. But from 2007-08 we are required to pay full tax after wiping out accumulated losses, said A.C. Mahajan, chairman and managing director of the bank.																								Total business as on September 30 stood at Rs 1,08,458 crore, a year-on-year growth of 19.87 per cent.																								Deposits grew 22.02 per cent to Rs 65,896 crore and advances went up 16.70 per cent to Rs 42,561 crore.																								The bank has also reduced its net non-performing assets to 0.75 per cent of its net advances from more than 1 per cent at the end of the previous fiscal. 
